Yeah, thanks, so, oh, I still have background, sorry about that. So I asked you at some point

00:16:40.479 --> 00:16:45.039
about advice for undergrad, and you mentioned, like, do a small GitHub repo, or, you know,

00:16:45.039 --> 00:16:50.880
profile, whatever. I think about this a lot, so what do you look for with, like, you know,

00:16:50.880 --> 00:16:55.760
undergrads, recent grads, you know, junior people, like, what are you looking for on those

00:16:55.760 --> 00:17:03.039
GitHub profiles? Oh, so, like, in, like, a portfolio? Yeah. Oh, sure, yeah. Yeah, I mean,

00:17:03.039 --> 00:17:10.719
it's gonna depend on, I guess I assume that the context is sort of, like, if I'm a hiring manager,

00:17:10.719 --> 00:17:16.959
and I'm looking to bring somebody in, so somebody is fresh out of school, they don't have any kind

00:17:16.959 --> 00:17:23.839
of, like, business experience, right, so I have to evaluate in some way the things you've done.

00:17:23.839 --> 00:17:31.119
So I would say, like, you know, if you've had some internship experience, you can list that

00:17:31.119 --> 00:17:35.280
experience, you can kind of tell me sort of, like, what are the things that you accomplished, you

00:17:35.280 --> 00:17:42.640
know, what were some of the things you were able to produce or deliver on, but if you just didn't

00:17:43.280 --> 00:17:46.800
get that internship experience, or, you know, you don't have things that you can sort of

00:17:46.800 --> 00:17:50.479
demonstrate on your resume, for example, it's great to have that portfolio, because

00:17:51.920 --> 00:17:57.760
what I'd be looking for is I want to just go in and see that, okay, you have, you know, some

00:17:57.760 --> 00:18:03.680
sort of, like, idea of structure of how the project should progress, so just the way I think about it

00:18:03.680 --> 00:18:13.040
is breaking projects into sort of data wrangling, cleaning some of the EDA processes, and then some

00:18:13.040 --> 00:18:18.239
of the modeling, and then some of the reporting, and then kind of tying it all together into

00:18:18.959 --> 00:18:24.800
a reproducible environment where I can sort of build that environment, I can see the steps

00:18:25.520 --> 00:18:31.119
to run to sort of execute and build that same model, and produce those outputs, and that

00:18:31.119 --> 00:18:35.359
kind of tells me you thought through the whole, like, end-to-end process, and you kind of thought

00:18:35.359 --> 00:18:40.000
through how is somebody else going to be able to take this and use it. That's probably where I would,

00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:43.119
I would say, like, that's a good portfolio project for data science in my mind.

